  <p>If you are offering people different routes, explain upfront any information they will need to have to hand so that they can make an informed choice. For example: "If you do this, you will need [whatever]." There is more information about this in <a href=""/service-manual/content/how-to-write-good-questions/6-write-the-supporting-content-for-your-form"">6. Write the supporting content for your form</a>.</p>
  <p>You may not need to collect answers to filter questions.</p>
  <p>Filter questions are useful but there are some things to bear in mind, especially with Yes No questions.</p>

<h2>Beware binary choices</h2>
<p>There are often more options than you think. For example, instead of asking "Do you know your NHS number?" with a Yes No answer, you might word it: "Can you find your NHS number?"</p>
<p>And the answers might be:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Yes, I have my NHS number</li>
  <li>I can find my NHS number</li>
  <li>I have an NHS number, but I can't find it</li>
  <li>I don't think I have an NHS number</li>
  <li>I don't know</li>
</ul>
<p>Sometimes you can test this by leaving a space for people to type in.</p>
<h2>Ask 1 question at a time</h2>
<p>Make sure you're asking 1 question at a time - not 2 questions in 1.</p>
<p>Here's an example of 2 in 1:</p>
<div class="app-example">
  <strong class="nhsuk-tag nhsuk-tag--dark-grey app-example__heading">Example</strong>
  <p>“If you have an email address, can we contact you about research?”</p>
</div>
<p>Here's an example of 3 questions in 1:</p>
<div class="app-example">
  <strong class="nhsuk-tag nhsuk-tag--dark-grey app-example__heading">Example</strong>
  <p>"If this questionnaire has highlighted any problems, how difficult have these problems made it for you to do your work, take care of things at home, or get along with other people?"</p>
</div>


<h2>Be clear what "Yes" and "No" mean</h2>
<p>Rather than simply offering "Yes" or "No" options, be clear.</p>

<div class="app-example nhsuk-u-margin-top-7 nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-7">
  <strong class="nhsuk-tag nhsuk-tag--dark-grey app-example__heading">Example</strong>
  {{ radios({
    "idPrefix": "example",
    "name": "example",
    "fieldset": {
      "legend": {
        "text": "Can we contact you by email about research?",
        "classes": "nhsuk-fieldset__legend--m"
      }
    },
    "items": [
      {
        "value": "yes",
        "text": "Yes, you can contact me by email about research"
      },
      {
        "value": "no",
        "text": "No, do not contact me about research"
      }
    ]
  }) }}
</div>

<p>In a simple Yes No question, "No" could also mean:<p>
<ul>
  <li>"No, do not contact me by email"</li>
  <li>"No, do not contact me at all"</li>
</ul>

<h2>Let users answer "I don't know" or "I'm not sure"</h2>

<p>In the research example above, users might want to say:</p>
<ul>
  <li>"I don't understand the question"</li>
  <li>"I only want to know about x research"</li>
</ul>

<div class="app-example nhsuk-u-margin-top-7 nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-7">
  <strong class="nhsuk-tag nhsuk-tag--dark-grey app-example__heading">Example</strong>
  {{ radios({
